  ('city:italy:rome', 'city', 'rome', 'tuscany-central', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Rome', 'Rome is a layered capital where ancient sites, piazzas, trattorias, wine bars, churches, boutique stays, and neighborhood routes through Trastevere, Monti, Prati, and Centro Storico set the pace. It works best on foot, with landmarks as the spine and meals or neighborhood detours keeping it from feeling dutiful.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:rome:rome:centro-storico', 'neighborhood', 'centro-storico', 'rome', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Centro Storico', 'Postcard Rome centered on the Pantheon, Piazza Navona, and Trevi Fountain, with dense historic streets and landmarks. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:rome:rome:trastevere', 'neighborhood', 'trastevere', 'rome', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Trastevere', 'Across the river, this is Rome''s most atmospheric neighborhood with ivy-covered walls and lively nightly trattorias. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:rome:rome:garbatella', 'neighborhood', 'garbatella', 'rome', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Garbatella', 'A character-rich residential quarter known for village-like streets, local food spots, and a more lived-in Roman feel. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:rome:rome:monti', 'neighborhood', 'monti', 'rome', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Monti', 'A trendy, bohemian pocket tucked right next to the Colosseum. It is full of vintage boutiques and craft beer bars. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:rome:rome:testaccio', 'neighborhood', 'testaccio', 'rome', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Testaccio', 'The "original" foodie neighborhood. It is less crowded and home to some of the best traditional Roman pasta dishes. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:rome:rome:prati', 'neighborhood', 'prati', 'rome', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Prati', 'The gateway to the Vatican. It is an elegant, orderly district ideal for visiting St. Peter''s Basilica and the Vatican Museums. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:rome:rome:celio', 'neighborhood', 'celio', 'rome', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Rome', 'Celio', 'The neighborhood around the Colosseum and nearby ancient ruins, with elevated viewpoints and quieter residential pockets. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('city:italy:milan', 'city', 'milan', 'north-lakes-alps', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Milan', 'Milan', 'Milan is a design and fashion city where aperitivo, contemporary art, shopping streets, polished hotels, restaurants, canals, and rail links make a sharp northern Italy base. The eating and drinking land best when they feel rooted in place, with enough neighborhood logic to carry a full day.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:milan:milan:brera', 'neighborhood', 'brera', 'milan', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Milan', 'Brera', 'Brera is Milan''s artful old-center quarter, where galleries, the Pinacoteca, boutiques, courtyards, aperitivo spots, and narrow streets keep the route elegant. It works best as a late-afternoon route, with browsing and art sliding naturally into aperitivo or dinner nearby.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:milan:milan:navigli', 'neighborhood', 'navigli', 'milan', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Milan', 'Navigli', 'Navigli is Milan''s canal-side social district, where aperitivo terraces, vintage shops, restaurants, and late bars make the city loosen after work. It works best in the evening, with canal walks and drinks timed before the busiest dinner stretch.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:milan:milan:porta-venezia', 'neighborhood', 'porta-venezia', 'milan', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Milan', 'Porta Venezia', 'Porta Venezia is Milan''s diverse eastside district, where Liberty architecture, gardens, queer nightlife, global food, and shopping corridors sit close together. It works best as a flexible route between park time, dinner, and drinks, especially when the center feels too polished.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:milan:milan:isola', 'neighborhood', 'isola', 'milan', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Milan', 'Isola', 'Isola is Milan''s northside design pocket, where new towers, old neighborhood streets, music rooms, restaurants, and creative studios meet around Garibaldi. It works best from afternoon into night, with architecture views balanced by smaller food and bar stops.'),
  ('neighborhood:italy:milan:milan:quadrilatero-doro', 'neighborhood', 'quadrilatero-doro', 'milan', 'Europe', 'Italy', 'Milan', 'Quadrilatero d''Oro', 'Quadrilatero d''Oro is a Milan neighborhood that works better as a tight route than as part of a broad citywide sweep. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
