  ('region:spain:spain:catalonia-barcelona', 'region', 'catalonia-barcelona', 'spain', 'Europe', 'Spain', null, 'Catalonia (Mediterranean Creative Coast)', 'Mediterranean city-and-coast routes with design, beach access, and regional culture.'),
  ('region:spain:spain:basque-north', 'region', 'basque-north', 'spain', 'Europe', 'Spain', null, 'Basque Country & Green North (Atlantic Food Trail)', 'Atlantic food regions, surf coastlines, and cooler northern landscapes.'),
  ('region:spain:spain:islands', 'region', 'islands', 'spain', 'Europe', 'Spain', null, 'Balearic & Canary Islands (Island Escape)', 'Island-focused travel for beach, cycling, and resort-to-local town itineraries.'),
  ('city:spain:barcelona', 'city', 'barcelona', 'catalonia-barcelona', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Barcelona', 'Barcelona', 'Barcelona is a dense Mediterranean city where Gothic lanes, Eixample''s Modernista landmarks, late tapas dinners, natural-wine bars, design hotels, social hostels, hilltop parks, and beachside days all sit within a few metro stops. The trick is making that richness practical without flattening it into a checklist.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:barcelona:barcelona:gothic-quarter', 'neighborhood', 'gothic-quarter', 'barcelona', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Barcelona', 'Gothic Quarter', 'The Gothic Quarter is Barcelona at its tightest: medieval lanes, cathedral squares, Roman fragments, and tourist pressure all packed into the old city. It works best when the route avoids aimless wandering, using a few historic anchors, quieter side streets, and selective food stops.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:barcelona:barcelona:el-born', 'neighborhood', 'el-born', 'barcelona', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Barcelona', 'El Born', 'El Born is Barcelona''s stylish old-town pocket, where Santa Maria del Mar, design shops, wine bars, narrow lanes, and the Picasso Museum sit close together. It works best from late afternoon into night, when browsing can turn into tapas, drinks, and slower nearby plaza time.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:barcelona:barcelona:eixample', 'neighborhood', 'eixample', 'barcelona', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Barcelona', 'Eixample', 'Eixample is Barcelona''s grand grid, where Modernista facades, Passeig de Gracia, polished hotels, and serious restaurants give the city its broadest rhythm. It works best for architecture-led days that need easy transit, strong dining, and room to reset between landmarks.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:barcelona:barcelona:gracia', 'neighborhood', 'gracia', 'barcelona', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Barcelona', 'Gracia', 'Gracia is the village-feeling Barcelona neighborhood where small plazas, independent shops, cafes, and local bars make the city feel less managed. It works best as a slower route, with short walks between squares and enough time to let dinner or drinks choose the next stop.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:barcelona:barcelona:poble-sec', 'neighborhood', 'poble-sec', 'barcelona', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Barcelona', 'Poble-sec', 'Poble-sec is Barcelona''s Montjuic-edge neighborhood, where theaters, tapas bars, Carrer de Blai, and hillside streets turn a compact area into an evening route. It works best when paired with park or museum time above it, then allowed to slide downhill into dinner and drinks.'),
  ('city:spain:madrid', 'city', 'madrid', 'madrid-castile', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Madrid', 'Madrid', 'Madrid is a late-running capital where big museums, tapas streets, market halls, vermouth bars, Retiro walks, galleries, and generous plazas set an easy rhythm. The route works best when daytime culture has room to loosen into La Latina, Chueca, or Malasana after dark nights.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:madrid:madrid:sol-centro', 'neighborhood', 'sol-centro', 'madrid', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Madrid', 'Sol & Centro', 'Madrid''s kilometer-zero core, anchored by Puerta del Sol, Plaza Mayor, and fast access to major historic landmarks. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:madrid:madrid:barrio-de-las-letras', 'neighborhood', 'barrio-de-las-letras', 'madrid', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Madrid', 'Barrio de las Letras', 'The Literary Quarter with writer heritage, elegant streets, and ideal positioning between the city''s major art museums. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:madrid:madrid:retiro', 'neighborhood', 'retiro', 'madrid', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Madrid', 'Retiro', 'A refined district beside El Retiro Park, perfect for green-space afternoons, museums, and polished central strolls. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:madrid:madrid:malasana', 'neighborhood', 'malasana', 'madrid', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Madrid', 'Malasana', 'A high-energy neighborhood known for vintage shops, indie cafes, and the nightlife legacy of Madrid''s Movida scene. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:madrid:madrid:la-latina', 'neighborhood', 'la-latina', 'madrid', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Madrid', 'La Latina', 'One of old Madrid''s most atmospheric quarters, famous for tapas streets and the Sunday El Rastro market. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
  ('neighborhood:spain:madrid:madrid:chueca', 'neighborhood', 'chueca', 'madrid', 'Europe', 'Spain', 'Madrid', 'Chueca', 'A vibrant, inclusive district with lively plazas, modern dining, and one of central Madrid''s strongest night scenes. It works best when the picks name a real cluster, street edge, park, market, waterfront, or night strip instead of spreading across the map.'),
