  ('country:japan', 'country', 'japan', 'asia', 'Asia', 'Japan', null, 'Japan', 'Japan is a destination in Asia shaped by capital hubs, deep food culture, temples or heritage sites, and wide regional variety. Use it for food, nightlife, nature, culture, stays, and activities across capitals and regional hubs, anchored by Tokyo and Kyoto. Regional routes extend the trip beyond the anchor city.'),
  ('city:japan:tokyo', 'city', 'tokyo', 'japan', 'Asia', 'Japan', 'Tokyo', 'Tokyo', 'Tokyo is a vast rail-connected city where ramen counters, sushi rooms, cocktail bars, shopping streets, design hotels, museums, gardens, and neighborhood micro-routes reward precision. It works best on foot, with landmarks as the spine and meals or neighborhood detours keeping it from feeling dutiful.'),
  ('neighborhood:japan:tokyo:tokyo:shibuya', 'neighborhood', 'shibuya', 'tokyo', 'Asia', 'Japan', 'Tokyo', 'Shibuya', 'Shibuya is Tokyo''s high-volume youth and shopping district, where crossings, department stores, music bars, ramen counters, and backstreets keep the pace fast. It works best after lunch into night, with one shopping or food anchor keeping the density from turning into pure drift.'),
  ('neighborhood:japan:tokyo:tokyo:shinjuku', 'neighborhood', 'shinjuku', 'tokyo', 'Asia', 'Japan', 'Tokyo', 'Shinjuku', 'Shinjuku is Tokyo''s vertical entertainment and transit machine, where neon alleys, department stores, hotel bars, gardens, and late food sit above one of the world''s busiest stations. It works best when split by mood: calm garden or shopping first, then a tighter evening route through food and drinks.'),
  ('neighborhood:japan:tokyo:tokyo:ginza', 'neighborhood', 'ginza', 'tokyo', 'Asia', 'Japan', 'Tokyo', 'Ginza', 'Ginza is Tokyo''s polished shopping and dining grid, where flagship stores, department basements, galleries, cocktail bars, and classic restaurants make luxury feel precise. It works best as a controlled afternoon or evening, with browsing, one reservation, and nearby drinks carrying the plan.'),
  ('neighborhood:japan:tokyo:tokyo:asakusa', 'neighborhood', 'asakusa', 'tokyo', 'Asia', 'Japan', 'Tokyo', 'Asakusa', 'Asakusa is Tokyo''s old-town visitor district, where Senso-ji, market streets, river views, and snack counters keep traditional city rhythms visible. It works best early or near dusk, with temple time balanced by food streets and a short walk toward the Sumida.'),
  ('neighborhood:japan:tokyo:tokyo:roppongi', 'neighborhood', 'roppongi', 'tokyo', 'Asia', 'Japan', 'Tokyo', 'Roppongi', 'Roppongi is Tokyo''s art, hotel, and nightlife district, where Mori Art Museum, design stops, embassies, restaurants, and late bars share the same hills. It works best as an evening route, with museum or view time leading into dinner and a selective late-night plan.'),
